      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s actually not thread safe, right?.  It\u0027s now (still) thread-compatible, just like most other data types.  \"Thread-safe\" kind of implies it\u0027s safe to mix calls to const and non-const methods on a object of this type from different threads without any other synchronization, and that\u0027s definitely not true.\n\nI think what this comment used to want to say is \"SkMatrix44 is thread-hostile unless you\u0027ve first called SkMatrix44::getType() to cache that calculation, and after that it\u0027s a normal thread-compatible type,\" but we should have probably just deleted this comment when Yuqian fixed the races in that other CL.",
      "revId": "dde6f3e8391dbe3bc3fcade8c419efe7b3a5e9c1",
